 Analyzing: Market landscape, competition and emerging customer trends
 Creating: Bring ideas to life through crisp, clear marketing content with an emphasis on customers and solving their problems and removing adoption barriers
 Communicating: Deliver ideas with confidence and clarity using slides, whiteboards, and other creative approaches
 Collaborating: Execute marketing plan by tapping into product management, marketing experts, campaign marketing, and engineering
 Engaging: Engage customers through sales tools, helping them make the right choices and nurture them with success stories
 What we need to see:
 Bachelors degree in engineering or computer science (or equivalent experience)
 10+ years of product marketing and/or product management experience along with prior experience as a software engineer building cutting edge software or hardware products
 Proven track record in growing responsibilities and/or consistent promotions
 Strong analytical and problem-solving skills to identify issues, opportunities, and more importantly, the ability to find solutions
 Proven track record of creating and executing product go-to-market strategies
 Excellent communication skills
 Ways to stand out from the crowd:
 Working knowledge of processor architectures as well as accelerated computing for machine learning, deep learning, high-performance computing
 Proven ability to lead and drive cross-organization teams, both to gather and present information to diverse groups
 Exceptional communication and presentation abilities
 MBA preferred but not required
